				<a href="/~Milo_Mindbender">Milo_Mindbender</a> writes <i>I'm trying to find a bulletproof near zero maintenance video conferencing client for shared use in an Alzheimers living facility.  It's used so the patients can regularly see their relatives who are often out of town.  Most everything I've tried on PC or Mac requires tweeks/updates from time to time to keep it working, not good in a place where there are no computer savvy people.  It looks like most of the low cost dedicated boxes have died out too.  The ideal setup will be turnkey with little-to-no maintenance and if possible support auto-answering calls from approved users.  It needs to be compatible with video conferencing apps the relatives can easily get on phone/tablet/pc such as Skype, Facetime, Hangouts...etc. Any suggestions?</i>
		 	
