<div class="body" id="fhbody-63035121">
	

	
		
		<div id="text-63035121" class="p">
			
		 	
				<a href="/~UrsaMajor987">UrsaMajor987 (3604759)</a> writes <i>I have a Asus Transformer tablet that I dropped on the floor. There is no obvious sign of damage but It will no longer boot. Good excuse to get a newer model. I intend to sell it for parts (it comes with an undamaged keyboard) or maybe just toss it. I want to remove all my personal data. I removed the flash memory card but what about the other storage?  I know how to wipe a hard drive, but how do you wipe a tablet?</i> If you were feeling especially paranoid, but wanted to keep the hardware intact for the next user, what would you do?
		 	
		</div>

		

		

		
